{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place red wine, sugar, honey, cinnamon sticks and cloves in mixing bowl. Arrange pears in Varoma dish and tray, set Varoma in position and steam <b>20-25 min\/Varoma\/î€ƒ\/speed 1<b> or until tender, adjusting steaming time according to type, size and ripeness of pears. Remove Varoma and set aside.","Strain spiced wine through simmering basket into a container (1 litre) and allow to cool. Place cooked pears in the container with spiced wine, cover and refrigerate for 2-3 hours, or 1-2 days for a deeper colour.","When ready to serve, remove container from fridge, place spiced wine in mixing bowl and, without measuring cup, reduce <b>15-20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> or until slightly thickened - it will thicken more as it cools. Serve pears with 1-2 tbsp hot or room-temperature wine reduction per portion."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["500 g red wine, fruity (e.g. Beaujolais)","100 g sugar","1 tsp honey","2 cinnamon sticks","3 cloves","800 g ripe pears, peeled, quartered and cored"]}],"id":"r150934","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-RcdGE2C-Jug\/XZWdWzyoAiI\/AAAAAAAAekg\/tUBWi1x-JTokq2LyovzjSI8FlX1h37LfwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_FeS0WPWBSP-bf3px.png","title":"Pears in Spiced Red Wine","publishedAt":"2017-06-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1 g","fat":"0 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"36 g","calories":"853 kJ \/ 204 kcal"},"usefulItems":"plastic container (1 litre), refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["For a faster result, omit <b>step 2<b> and reduce spiced wine immediately, without marinating pears. In this case, pears will remain white.<br>- You can vary the spices in the wine according to your preference (e.g. star anise, vanilla).","<i>This easy dessert is fresh and aromatic and can be served in many ways. The pears develop a deep red colour after a day or two in the spiced wine, and if preserved as described in the tips they make a lovely homemade gift.<\/i>","Serve pears with sabayon (zabaglione) or a scoop of vanilla ice cream.<br>- Store in the fridge and serve within <b>7 days<b>.<br>- Pears can be preserved: add <b>300 g water<b> in <b>step 1,<b> then in <b>step 2<b> place cooked pears in warm sterilised jars and pour hot spiced wine into jars to cover the pears. Seal immediately and turn upside down for <b>10 minutes.<b> Preserved pears can be stored refrigerated for a few weeks, and must be eaten within <b>7 days<b> of opening the jar.<br>- For a sweet-savoury combination, serve pears in red wine with Gorgonzola cheese as a starter or cheese course."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","3h 20m","6 portions"]}